(388, 1, '2016-07-14 08:11:07', '2016-07-14 08:11:07', 'Builderry Construction Company served as the Construction Manager for this 150-beds hospital, located in the northern part of Albuquerqe, NM. Extensive on-site work, including pilings, was required for this project. We''ve faced a brutal winter weather, along with the hospital location along the Rio Grande shoreline. Though such forces of nature challenged the construction team, we managed to build the project few weeks ahead of the schedule!\r\n<h4>Some of the tasks that we successfully completed during the construction:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>New emergency room complex with eight emergency examining rooms, two trauma rooms, and auxiliary areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Twelve (12) new patient rooms</li>\r\n 	<li>Four new (4) labor and delivery rooms</li>\r\n 	<li>New nursery</li>\r\n 	<li>New administrative, maintenance, housekeeping and training rooms</li>\r\n 	<li>New ambulance entrance with heated concrete</li>\r\n 	<li>New helicopter landing pad (heated aluminum deck) above the E.R. entrance with an 8,500 lb. capacity. The only one of its kind in a 60-mile radius.</li>\r\n 	<li>Heated sidewalks, driveways, and receiving dock</li>\r\n 	<li>Renovation of the Radiology Department</li>\r\n 	<li>The new addition totaled 47,000 sq.ft. and renovations encompassed approximately 10,000 sq.ft.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Albuquerque City  Hospital', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'albuquerque-city-hospital', '', '', '2016-09-20 12:18:29', '2016-09-20 12:18:29', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=388', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(393, 1, '2016-07-14 09:08:57', '2016-07-14 09:08:57', 'This new 91,000 sq.ft building offers flexible, state-of-the-art classrooms, a spacious and technically advanced laboratory and clinical spaces, comfortable faculty offices and administrative spaces. That''s a new for the Memphis State University after a grand renovation that our team has undertaken!\r\n\r\nBesides working on enhancing the look of the main buildings and campuses, we also spruced up the current facilities which hold all the departments. The full list includes distance learning facilities; a teaching auditorium; and a student, faculty and staff lounge/library...\r\n\r\nWe used numerous types of building materials, including reinforced concrete masonry units and brick veneer with structural steel framing. Also, our construction workers managed to integrate the state-of-the-art voice and data communication systems into the main building''s walls.\r\n\r\nAdditional works included new parking lots area as well as landscaping design and constructing...', 'Memphis State University', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'memphis-state-university', '', '', '2016-09-05 13:38:10', '2016-09-05 13:38:10', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=393', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(395, 1, '2016-07-14 09:16:00', '2016-07-14 09:16:00', 'Building this tower took us a lot of effort and a lot of creative input. When Mr. Trump initially placed this order, we''ve been puzzled...\r\n\r\nThe creativity and boldness of the conceptual sketch required an expertise from all our designers, engineers and architects to get it completed.\r\n<h4>Some of the tasks that we successfully completed during the construction:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completing a high-rise in an unfriendly terrain</li>\r\n 	<li>Beating the initial schedule by 1 month</li>\r\n 	<li>Cutting the final budget by $2 million</li>\r\n 	<li>Making the height of the final building 10 feet taller than the sketch even dared to propose</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Trump''s Biggest Tower in Arlington, Virginia', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'trumps-biggest-tower-in-arlington-virginia', '', '', '2016-09-05 13:38:06', '2016-09-05 13:38:06', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=395', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(397, 1, '2016-07-14 09:20:27', '2016-07-14 09:20:27', 'When the auto manufacturer Tesla motors decided to build a brand new factory in a desert, ground up, we''ve been proud to participate and win in the contest to become the vendors.\r\n\r\nSince then, we''re still working on this incredibly intricate and sizable construction site. To give you a glimpse into how ambitious the factory is, we can tell you that more than 1000 construction workers partake in the on-site construction process, daily!\r\n<h4>Some of the tasks that we successfully completed during the construction:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Successfully bringing lines of communication into a desert area</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintaining a schedule, despite numerous nature inflicted delays and issues</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Tesla''s Gigafactory', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'teslas-gigafactory', '', '', '2016-09-05 13:38:03', '2016-09-05 13:38:03', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=397', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(399, 1, '2016-07-14 09:23:13', '2016-07-14 09:23:13', 'While we''ve had a great deal of experience in building IT related buildings, office and data centers before, this project challenged us to the core.\r\n\r\nIt took us four good years to build, but eventually it all paid off, as the end building with all the tweaks and additions that our engineers, architects and designers envisioned turned out to be more functional, than the initial blueprint!\r\n<h4>Some of the IT companies that we''ve built buildings for:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Yahoo</li>\r\n 	<li>Google</li>\r\n 	<li>Microsoft</li>\r\n 	<li>Yelp</li>\r\n 	<li>Baidu</li>\r\n 	<li>FourSquare</li>\r\n 	<li>Twitter</li>\r\n 	<li>Oracle</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Yahoo''s Data Center', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'yahoos-data-center', '', '', '2016-09-05 13:38:00', '2016-09-05 13:38:00', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=399', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(401, 1, '2016-07-14 09:24:43', '2016-07-14 09:24:43', 'As we initially took this project onboard, we were ready for all kinds of issues to pop up and prevent us from completing it on time...\r\n\r\nJust to mention, a shipyard size itself can be a demoralizing experience for any project manager... Nevertheless, we''ve managed to get it completed on time!\r\n<h4>Some of the tasks that we successfully completed during the construction:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Improving the maritime infrastructure around the shipyard and the city of Norfolk</li>\r\n 	<li>Working around the issue with working on it during a hurricanes rich autumn and a cold, snowy winter</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Navy shipyard #123, Norfolk, VA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'navy-shipyard-123-norfolk-va', '', '', '2016-09-19 11:59:21', '2016-09-19 11:59:21', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=401', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(403, 1, '2016-07-14 09:27:20', '2016-07-14 09:27:20', 'One big advantage that Chicago has, is the huge size of its metropolitan area, also known as the "Chicagoland". Having a population close to 12 million people, this area expands rapidly, and needs diligence in managing...\r\n\r\nSo when the state of Illinois chosen us to work on the landscape design and construction for one of the new parks, we''ve been eager to accept it!\r\n<h4>Some of the tasks that we successfully completed during the construction:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Creating a new green zone in a densely populated living area</li>\r\n 	<li>Incorporating it into the current architectural ensemble of the district</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Chicagoland Recreational Park, IL', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'chicagoland-recreational-park-il', '', '', '2016-09-19 12:29:10', '2016-09-19 12:29:10', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=403', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
(405, 1, '2016-07-14 09:29:00', '2016-07-14 09:29:00', 'It''s now wonder that such a global Internet retailer as Amazon builds new warehouses time to time... This year they were looking to get a brand new Midwest warehouse in South Dakota.\r\n\r\nThat was when we stepped in, previously building similar (though a bit smaller) warehouses for miscellaneous companies...\r\n<h4>Some interesting trivia about the construction process:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>People working there walk an average of 13 miles per day. That''s why we''ve built few moving staircases and have made few tracks inclined - to help people cicrumvent the warehouse faster</li>\r\n 	<li>We''ve built in a lot of advanced, "smart" shelves inside the sidewalls, to save on space</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Amazon''s Warehouse, SD', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'amazons-warehouse-sd', '', '', '2016-09-19 12:23:53', '2016-09-19 12:23:53', '', 0, 'http://192.168.0.100/work/16.10.20/caldera/?post_type=projects&#038;p=405', 0, 'projects', '', 0),
